50|$|Abu Ayadh aka ben Hassine founded <b>Ansar</b> <b>al-Sharia</b> <b>in</b> late April 2011. The group quickly {{established}} a media branch, al-Qairawan Media Foundation, and developed different media outlets including a blog, Facebook page, and a magazine. <b>Ansar</b> <b>al-Sharia</b> held a national conference at Kairouan in 2012 in which Abu Ayadh aka ben Hassine {{called for the}} Islamization of Tunisia's media, education, tourism and commercial sectors, {{and the establishment of}} an Islamic trade union to confront the secular Tunisian General Labour Union. The group also campaigned for the release of Islamist prisoners, such as Omar Abdel-Rahman, Abu Qatada and Tunisians who had fought with al-Qaeda in Iraq and are held in Iraqi jails.|$|R
