50|$|In a 2013 report, Foundation for Defense of Democracies {{senior fellow}} Daveed Gartenstein-Ross {{reported}} presumed links between Belhadj and <b>Ansar</b> <b>al-Sharia,</b> the Tunisian salafi jihadist group. Gartenstein-Ross wrote that a Tunisian investigator accused Abdelhakim Belhadj of sheltering <b>Ansar</b> <b>al-Sharia</b> leader Abu Iyadh al-Tunisi {{after the murder}} of two Tunisian opposition leaders Chokri Belaïd and Mohamed Brahmi. <b>Ansar</b> <b>al-Sharia</b> is regarded as responsible for {{the assassination of the}} two politicians.|$|R
